    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-17T10:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-17T10:30:00-05:00" n="503"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">833.6463/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-17T12:00:00-03:30"
                            >May 17, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>195. My number 190, May 14, 6 p.m. Guani handed me last night a <hi rend="italic"
                        >note verbale</hi> containing the promised memorandum from Rione clarifying
                    the relationship between the Uruguayan Government and the German Consortium with
                    regard to the Rio Negro Hydroelectric Project. Although the Rione memorandum has
                    already been sent to the Uruguayan Minister in Washington for presentation to
                    the Department, the Legation is forwarding copies in today’s airmail pouch.<note
                        n="72" xml:id="d503fn72">Despatch No. 970 and enclosed <hi rend="italic"
                            >note verbale</hi>, not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Department’s attention is especially invited to items 2 and 5 of the Rione’s
                    memorandum from which it is clear that while the proposed contract with American
                    interests for 1 turbo generator and <pb facs="0608" n="600" xml:id="pg_600"/>
                    equipment is considered a separate contract the Rione does not contemplate the
                    elimination of German interests in other phases of the project and that in fact
                    German personnel will continue to work on the project.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
